>
  <p class="support-lead">This page summarizes our standard limited warranty for B2B customers. The binding warranty for any specific order is the one stated in your quotation, order confirmation or sales agreement.</p>

  <h2>Coverage</h2>
  <p>GYUTRON warrants that its hardware products are free from defects in materials and workmanship under normal industrial use for the warranty period stated on the applicable quotation or datasheet — typically <strong>twelve (12) months from delivery</strong> unless a different period is agreed in writing. During this period GYUTRON will, at its discretion, repair or replace a product found to be defective.</p>

  <h2>What is covered</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Defects in materials and workmanship under normal use within the product's published specifications.</li>
    <li>Repair or replacement with new or equivalent refurbished parts/products at GYUTRON's discretion.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What is not covered</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Misuse, improper installation, operation outside published specifications, or inadequate maintenance.</li>
    <li>Unauthorized modification, disassembly or repair.</li>
    <li>Accidental, physical, electrical or liquid damage, including exposure beyond the product's stated IP rating.</li>
    <li>Consumables and wear parts (for example batteries, cables, gaskets) and cosmetic wear such as scratches.</li>
    <li>Damage caused by third-party accessories, power anomalies, or force majeure.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>RMA process</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>1. Contact support.</strong> Email <a href="mailto:info@gyutron.com">info@gyutron.com</a> with the product model, serial number, and a description of the fault (with photos, logs or sample images where possible).</li>
    <li><strong>2. Receive an RMA number.</strong> Our team will review the case and, if eligible, issue a Return Merchandise Authorization with return instructions.</li>
    <li><strong>3. Return the unit.</strong> Pack the product securely (ESD protection where applicable) and ship it per the RMA instructions.</li>
    <li><strong>4. Inspection &amp; resolution.</strong> After inspection we will repair, replace or return the unit and keep you informed of status.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Out-of-warranty service</h2>
  <p>Repair and service remain available for products outside the warranty period or for non-covered conditions, on a paid basis. Contact support for an assessment and quotation.</p>

  <div class="support-note">This warranty is provided to business customers and the exclusive remedy is repair or replacement as described above. It does not affect any statutory rights that cannot be excluded under applicable law, and is subject to the terms of your sales agreement.</div>
</SupportPage>
